A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing March 9 to 15, 2025, as Multiple Sclerosis Awareness Week at the state capitol;
2 and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, multiple sclerosis (MS) is a neurological disease of the central nervous system,
4 affecting nearly 1 million people in the United States alone; and
5 WHEREAS, MS generally strikes people in the prime of their life, between the ages of 20
6 to 50; the cause and course of the often debilitating symptoms of MS remain unknown; and
7 no cure currently exists; and
8 WHEREAS, the National Multiple Sclerosis Society is committed to a world free of MS,
9 heightening public knowledge about and insight into the disease; and
10 WHEREAS, together we have transformed what it means to live with MS and provided
11 global leadership to help achieve our vision of a world free of MS; and
12 WHEREAS, since 1946, the National Multiple Sclerosis Society has been a driving force of
13 MS research, relentlessly pursuing prevention, treatments, and a cure, and it has invested
14 more than $1 billion in groundbreaking research; and
