15 WHEREAS, funds raised through the National Multiple Sclerosis Society fuel research on
16 pathways to MS cures and invest in the MS research workforce at the best medical centers,
17 universities, and other institutions throughout the United States and abroad, leading to many
18 breakthroughs in the treatment of MS; and
19 WHEREAS, the mission of the National Multiple Sclerosis Society is to cure MS while
20 empowering people affected by MS to live their best lives, a goal that all Americans and
21 Georgians should support; and
22 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia recognizes the importance of finding the cause and cure
23 of MS and expresses its appreciation for the dedication that the National Multiple Sclerosis
24 Society - Georgia Chapter has shown toward creating a world free of MS.
25 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
26 recognize March 9 to 15, 2025, as Multiple Sclerosis Awareness Week at the state capitol
27 and encourage all citizens to learn more about the disease and what actions they can take to
28 support individuals with multiple sclerosis as well as their families.
29 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
30 to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the public and the
31 press.
